('w_cooking_A2_26','grill','/ɡrɪl/','verb','굽다 (그릴에)','To cook food on a grill using direct heat.','He likes to {grill} vegetables in summer.','그는 여름에 채소를 그릴에 굽는 것을 좋아해요.','grill','A2','cooking',1,'grill outdoor vegetables summer heat'),
('w_cooking_A2_27','roast','/roʊst/','verb','오븐에 굽다','To cook food in an oven with dry heat.','She will {roast} the chicken with herbs for dinner.','그녀는 저녁으로 허브를 곁들여 닭을 구울 거예요.','roast','A2','cooking',1,'roast chicken oven golden herbs'),
('w_cooking_A2_28','stir','/stɜːr/','verb','젓다','To move food in a circular motion while cooking.','{Stir} the sauce continuously to stop it burning.','소스가 타지 않도록 계속 저어 주세요.','Stir','A2','cooking',1,'stir sauce spoon pan cooking'),
('w_cooking_A2_29','pour','/pɔːr/','verb','붓다','To cause liquid to flow from a container.','{Pour} the stock slowly into the pan.','육수를 팬에 천천히 부어 주세요.','Pour','A2','cooking',1,'pour liquid pan stock cooking'),
('w_cooking_A2_30','serve','/sɜːrv/','verb','제공하다','To present food to someone to eat.','{Serve} the pasta while it is still hot.','파스타가 아직 뜨거울 때 제공해 주세요.','Serve','A2','cooking',1,'serve pasta plate hot table'),
('w_cooking_A2_31','flavor','/ˈfleɪvər/','noun','풍미','The taste of food or drink.','The soup has a rich, deep {flavor}.','이 수프는 풍부하고 깊은 풍미가 있어요.','flavor','A2','cooking',1,'flavor taste soup rich cooking'),
('w_cooking_A2_32','sour','/ˈsaʊər/','adjective','신','Having an acidic or sharp taste.','The yogurt has a slightly {sour} taste.','요거트는 약간 신맛이 나요.','sour','A2','cooking',1,'sour lemon yogurt acidic taste'),
('w_cooking_A2_33','salty','/ˈsɔːlti/','adjective','짠','Having a taste of salt.','The soup was too {salty} for her liking.','그 수프는 그녀가 좋아하기에 너무 짜요.','salty','A2','cooking',1,'salty soup seasoning taste cooking'),
