('w_cooking_B1_02','marinade','/ˈmærɪneɪd/','noun','마리네이드','A mixture of liquid and spices used to soak food before cooking.','Leave the meat in the {marinade} overnight.','고기를 마리네이드에 하룻밤 재워 주세요.','marinade','B1','cooking',1,'marinade meat soak spice liquid'),
('w_cooking_B1_03','simmer','/ˈsɪmər/','verb','약불에 끓이다','To cook food in liquid just below boiling point.','Let the sauce {simmer} for 20 minutes on low heat.','소스를 약불에서 20분 동안 끓여 주세요.','simmer','B1','cooking',1,'simmer pot low heat steam sauce'),
('w_cooking_B1_04','steam','/stiːm/','verb','찌다','To cook food using hot steam rather than water or oil.','{Steam} the broccoli for five minutes to keep it crisp.','브로콜리를 바삭하게 유지하려면 5분 동안 쪄 주세요.','Steam','B1','cooking',1,'steam broccoli basket pot healthy'),
('w_cooking_B1_05','deep-fry','/ˌdiːp ˈfraɪ/','verb','튀기다','To cook food by submerging it in hot oil.','He {deep-fries} the chicken until it is golden brown.','그는 닭이 황금갈색이 될 때까지 튀겨요.','deep-fries','B1','cooking',1,'deep fry oil golden crispy cooking'),
('w_cooking_B1_06','sauté','/sɔːˈteɪ/','verb','살짝 볶다','To fry food quickly in a small amount of fat over high heat.','{Sauté} the mushrooms in butter until they are tender.','버섯이 부드러워질 때까지 버터에 살짝 볶아 주세요.','Sauté','B1','cooking',1,'sauté mushroom butter pan quick'),
('w_cooking_B1_07','blend','/blɛnd/','verb','블렌딩하다','To mix ingredients together smoothly using a blender.','{Blend} the soup until it is completely smooth.','수프가 완전히 부드러워질 때까지 블렌딩해 주세요.','Blend','B1','cooking',1,'blend blender soup smooth cooking'),
('w_cooking_B1_08','whisk','/wɪsk/','verb','거품기로 섞다','To stir ingredients rapidly using a whisk.','{Whisk} the eggs and cream together until fluffy.','달걀과 크림을 폭신해질 때까지 거품기로 섞어 주세요.','Whisk','B1','cooking',1,'whisk eggs cream fluffy baking'),
('w_cooking_B1_09','knead','/niːd/','verb','반죽하다','To press and stretch dough with your hands.','{Knead} the bread dough for at least ten minutes.','빵 반죽을 최소 10분 이상 반죽해 주세요.','Knead','B1','cooking',1,'knead dough bread hands baking'),
('w_cooking_B1_10','measure','/ˈmɛʒər/','verb','계량하다','To find the exact amount of an ingredient.','Always {measure} the ingredients before you start baking.','베이킹을 시작하기 전에 항상 재료를 계량해 주세요.','measure','B1','cooking',1,'measure cup spoon baking ingredient'),
('w_cooking_B1_11','portion','/ˈpɔːrʃən/','noun','1인분','A single amount of food for one person.','Each {portion} should weigh around 200 grams.','1인분은 약 200그램이어야 해요.','portion','B1','cooking',1,'portion serving plate scale meal'),
('w_cooking_B1_12','leftover','/ˈlɛftˌoʊvər/','noun','남은 음식','Food that remains after a meal and is stored for later.','She turns {leftovers} into a completely new meal.','그녀는 남은 음식으로 완전히 새로운 요리를 만들어요.','leftovers','B1','cooking',1,'leftover container store fridge meal'),
('w_cooking_B1_13','refrigerate','/rɪˈfrɪdʒəreɪt/','verb','냉장 보관하다','To keep food cold in a refrigerator to prevent spoiling.','Always {refrigerate} dairy products after opening.','유제품은 개봉 후 항상 냉장 보관해 주세요.','refrigerate','B1','cooking',1,'refrigerate fridge dairy storage cold'),
('w_cooking_B1_14','freeze','/friːz/','verb','냉동하다','To preserve food at a very low temperature.','You can {freeze} the soup for up to three months.','수프는 최대 3개월까지 냉동할 수 있어요.','freeze','B1','cooking',1,'freeze container storage food preservation'),
('w_cooking_B1_15','thaw','/θɔː/','verb','해동하다','To allow frozen food to become soft and liquid at room temperature.','{Thaw} the meat in the refrigerator overnight.','고기는 냉장고에서 하룻밤 해동해 주세요.','Thaw','B1','cooking',1,'thaw frozen meat defrost refrigerator'),
('w_cooking_B1_16','grocery','/ˈɡroʊsəri/','noun','식료품','Food and household products bought at a shop.','She makes a weekly {grocery} list before shopping.','그녀는 쇼핑 전에 주간 식료품 목록을 작성해요.','grocery','B1','cooking',1,'grocery list shopping supermarket food'),
('w_cooking_B1_17','pantry','/ˈpæntri/','noun','식료품 저장실','A small room or cupboard for storing food.','Check the {pantry} for any canned goods we need.','필요한 통조림이 있는지 식료품 저장실을 확인해 주세요.','pantry','B1','cooking',1,'pantry storage shelves canned goods'),
('w_cooking_B1_18','herbs','/hɜːrbz/','noun','허브','Aromatic plants used to flavour food.','Fresh {herbs} add brightness to any dish.','신선한 허브는 모든 요리에 활력을 더해 줘요.','herbs','B1','cooking',1,'herbs fresh green aromatic cooking'),
('w_cooking_B1_19','spices','/ˈspaɪsɪz/','noun','향신료','Seeds, bark, or dried plants used to flavour food.','She keeps many {spices} in small jars on her shelf.','그녀는 선반에 작은 병에 많은 향신료를 보관해요.','spices','B1','cooking',1,'spices jars shelf aromatic colorful'),
('w_cooking_B1_20','vinegar','/ˈvɪnɪɡər/','noun','식초','A sour liquid used to season and preserve food.','Add a splash of {vinegar} to balance the sweetness.','단맛의 균형을 맞추려면 식초를 조금 넣어 주세요.','vinegar','B1','cooking',1,'vinegar bottle sour seasoning salad'),
('w_cooking_B1_21','lemon','/ˈlɛmən/','noun','레몬','A yellow citrus fruit with a sour juice used in cooking.','Squeeze half a {lemon} over the fish before serving.','생선을 내기 전에 레몬 반 개를 짜 주세요.','lemon','B1','cooking',1,'lemon yellow citrus squeeze cooking'),
('w_cooking_B1_22','lime','/laɪm/','noun','라임','A small green citrus fruit used in cooking and drinks.','Add {lime} juice to the sauce for extra acidity.','소스에 라임 즙을 넣어 산도를 더해 주세요.','lime','B1','cooking',1,'lime green citrus juice cooking'),
('w_cooking_B1_23','broth','/brɒθ/','noun','육수','A thin liquid made by simmering meat or vegetables.','Use chicken {broth} as the base for the soup.','수프의 베이스로 닭 육수를 사용해 주세요.','broth','B1','cooking',1,'broth liquid chicken soup base'),
('w_cooking_B1_24','stock','/stɒk/','noun','스톡 (진한 육수)','A flavourful liquid made by simmering bones and vegetables.','Homemade {stock} gives the stew a richer flavour.','집에서 만든 스톡을 쓰면 스튜가 더 풍부한 맛이 나요.','stock','B1','cooking',1,'stock pot bones simmering liquid'),
('w_cooking_B1_25','stew','/stjuː/','noun','스튜','A dish of meat and vegetables cooked slowly in liquid.','She cooks the beef {stew} for three hours on low heat.','그녀는 소고기 스튜를 약불에서 3시간 동안 끓여요.','stew','B1','cooking',1,'stew pot meat vegetable slow'),
('w_cooking_B1_26','casserole','/ˈkæsərəʊl/','noun','캐서롤','A dish cooked slowly in an oven in a covered pot.','The chicken {casserole} smells wonderful while it bakes.','닭 캐서롤이 오븐에 구워지는 동안 굉장히 향기로워요.','casserole','B1','cooking',1,'casserole dish oven slow baked'),
('w_cooking_B1_27','batter','/ˈbætər/','noun','반죽 (묽은)','A liquid mixture of flour, eggs, and milk used for cooking.','Dip the fish in the {batter} before frying it.','생선을 튀기기 전에 반죽에 담가 주세요.','batter','B1','cooking',1,'batter liquid dipping fish frying'),
('w_cooking_B1_28','dough','/doʊ/','noun','반죽 (도우)','A thick mixture of flour and liquid used to make bread or pastry.','Let the {dough} rest for one hour before shaping it.','반죽을 성형하기 전에 1시간 동안 쉬게 해 주세요.','dough','B1','cooking',1,'dough bread flour shaping baking'),
('w_cooking_B1_29','yeast','/jiːst/','noun','이스트','A microorganism that makes dough rise when baking bread.','Add the {yeast} to warm water and let it activate.','이스트를 따뜻한 물에 넣고 활성화시켜 주세요.','yeast','B1','cooking',1,'yeast bread baking rise ferment'),
('w_cooking_B1_30','rise','/raɪz/','verb','부풀다','For dough to expand due to yeast activity.','Leave the dough to {rise} for about one hour.','반죽을 약 1시간 동안 부풀게 두어 주세요.','rise','B1','cooking',1,'rise dough bread yeast expand'),
('w_cooking_B1_31','preheat','/ˌpriːˈhiːt/','verb','예열하다','To heat an oven to the required temperature before using it.','Always {preheat} the oven to 180°C before baking.','베이킹 전에 항상 오븐을 180°C로 예열해 주세요.','preheat','B1','cooking',1,'preheat oven temperature baking heat'),
('w_cooking_B1_32','oven','/ˈʌvən/','noun','오븐','An enclosed appliance used for baking and roasting.','Place the tray in the {oven} and bake for 25 minutes.','트레이를 오븐에 넣고 25분 동안 구워 주세요.','oven','B1','cooking',1,'oven kitchen baking appliance heat'),
('w_cooking_B1_33','temperature','/ˈtɛmprɪtʃər/','noun','온도','The degree of heat in cooking.','Check the internal {temperature} of the meat before serving.','고기를 내기 전에 내부 온도를 확인해 주세요.','temperature','B1','cooking',1,'temperature thermometer meat cooking degree'),
('w_cooking_B1_34','shelf life','/ˈʃɛlf laɪf/','noun','유통기한','The length of time food remains safe and suitable to use.','The {shelf life} of fresh pasta is only three days.','신선한 파스타의 유통기한은 3일뿐이에요.','shelf life','B1','cooking',1,'shelf life expiry label food storage'),
('w_cooking_B1_35','expiry','/ɪkˈspaɪəri/','noun','만료 (유통)','The time after which something is no longer safe to use.','Check the {expiry} date before using the yogurt.','요거트를 사용하기 전에 유통기한을 확인해 주세요.','expiry','B1','cooking',1,'expiry date label food safety'),
('w_cooking_B2_01','cuisine','/kwɪˈziːn/','noun','요리 (양식)','A style of cooking associated with a particular country or region.','French {cuisine} is known for its rich sauces and techniques.','프랑스 요리는 풍부한 소스와 기법으로 유명해요.','cuisine','B2','cooking',1,'cuisine french restaurant fine dining'),
('w_cooking_B2_02','culinary','/ˈkʌlɪnəri/','adjective','요리의','Relating to cooking or the kitchen.','She attended a {culinary} school in Paris.','그녀는 파리에서 요리 학교에 다녔어요.','culinary','B2','cooking',1,'culinary school chef cooking professional'),
('w_cooking_B2_03','technique','/tɛkˈniːk/','noun','기법','A skilled method of doing something.','Mastering the right {technique} makes all the difference in cooking.','올바른 기법을 익히면 요리가 크게 달라져요.','technique','B2','cooking',1,'technique chef skill cooking professional'),
('w_cooking_B2_04','presentation','/ˌprɛzənˈteɪʃən/','noun','플레이팅 (음식 표현)','The way in which food is arranged and displayed on a plate.','Beautiful {presentation} makes the meal more appealing.','아름다운 플레이팅은 식사를 더욱 매력적으로 만들어요.','presentation','B2','cooking',1,'presentation plate beautiful fine dining'),
('w_cooking_B2_05','plating','/ˈpleɪtɪŋ/','noun','플레이팅 (기술)','The technique of arranging food attractively on a plate.','Chef-level {plating} requires both skill and creativity.','셰프 수준의 플레이팅에는 기술과 창의력이 필요해요.','plating','B2','cooking',1,'plating plate chef artistic restaurant'),
('w_cooking_B2_06','garnish','/ˈɡɑːrnɪʃ/','verb','가니시하다','To decorate a dish with a small piece of food.','She {garnishes} each plate with a sprig of fresh mint.','그녀는 각 접시에 신선한 민트 한 줄기로 장식해요.','garnishes','B2','cooking',1,'garnish mint herb plate decoration'),
('w_cooking_B2_07','reduction','/rɪˈdʌkʃən/','noun','리덕션 (농축 소스)','A sauce made by boiling liquid until it thickens.','Drizzle the balsamic {reduction} over the salad.','샐러드 위에 발사믹 리덕션을 뿌려 주세요.','reduction','B2','cooking',1,'reduction sauce balsamic drizzle plate'),
('w_cooking_B2_08','caramelize','/ˈkærəməlaɪz/','verb','캐러멜화하다','To heat sugar or food until it turns golden and sweet.','{Caramelize} the onions slowly for a rich, sweet flavour.','풍부하고 달콤한 맛을 위해 양파를 천천히 캐러멜화해 주세요.','Caramelize','B2','cooking',1,'caramelize onion golden brown sweet pan'),
('w_cooking_B2_09','deglaze','/diːˈɡleɪz/','verb','디글레이즈하다','To add liquid to a hot pan to loosen browned food bits.','{Deglaze} the pan with white wine after searing the meat.','고기를 굽고 나서 화이트와인으로 팬을 디글레이즈해 주세요.','Deglaze','B2','cooking',1,'deglaze pan wine sear flavor sauce'),
('w_cooking_B2_10','emulsify','/ɪˈmʌlsɪfaɪ/','verb','유화시키다','To combine oil and water-based ingredients into a smooth mixture.','Whisk vigorously to {emulsify} the dressing.','드레싱을 유화시키려면 힘차게 저어 주세요.','emulsify','B2','cooking',1,'emulsify dressing oil whisk smooth'),
('w_cooking_B2_11','poach','/poʊtʃ/','verb','포칭하다','To cook food gently in simmering liquid.','{Poach} the egg in barely simmering water for three minutes.','달걀을 약하게 끓는 물에 3분 동안 포칭해 주세요.','Poach','B2','cooking',1,'poach egg water gentle cooking'),
('w_cooking_B2_12','blanch','/blæntʃ/','verb','데치다','To briefly cook food in boiling water then cool it rapidly.','{Blanch} the green beans to preserve their bright colour.','초록 빛깔을 유지하려면 그린빈을 데쳐 주세요.','Blanch','B2','cooking',1,'blanch green beans boiling ice bath'),
('w_cooking_B2_13','braise','/breɪz/','verb','브레이징하다','To cook food slowly in a small amount of liquid in a covered pot.','{Braise} the beef short ribs for three hours until tender.','소고기 쇼트립이 부드러워질 때까지 3시간 동안 브레이징해 주세요.','Braise','B2','cooking',1,'braise beef pot slow liquid tender'),
('w_cooking_B2_14','flambé','/flɒmˈbeɪ/','verb','플람베하다','To pour alcohol over food and ignite it for flavour.','The chef {flamb​és} the crêpes tableside for a dramatic effect.','셰프는 극적인 효과를 위해 테이블 앞에서 크레이프를 플람베해요.','flambés','B2','cooking',1,'flambe fire alcohol dramatic chef'),
('w_cooking_B2_15','ferment','/fərˈmɛnt/','verb','발효하다','To allow microorganisms to break down food or drink.','She leaves the mixture to {ferment} for five days.','그녀는 혼합물을 5일 동안 발효시켜요.','ferment','B2','cooking',1,'ferment jar natural process preservation'),
('w_cooking_B2_16','preserve','/prɪˈzɜːrv/','verb','보존하다','To treat food to prevent it from decaying.','She {preserves} summer fruit as jam for winter.','그녀는 여름 과일을 잼으로 만들어 겨울을 위해 보존해요.','preserves','B2','cooking',1,'preserve jam jar summer fruit'),
('w_cooking_B2_17','pickle','/ˈpɪkəl/','verb','절이다','To preserve food in vinegar or brine.','He {pickles} cucumbers with garlic and dill.','그는 마늘과 딜을 넣어 오이를 절여요.','pickles','B2','cooking',1,'pickle cucumber vinegar jar brine'),
('w_cooking_B2_18','cure','/kjʊər/','verb','염장하다 / 훈제하다','To preserve meat or fish using salt, smoke, or sugar.','They {cure} the salmon with salt, sugar, and dill.','그들은 소금, 설탕, 딜로 연어를 염장해요.','cure','B2','cooking',1,'cure salmon salt preservation method'),
('w_cooking_B2_19','smoke','/smoʊk/','verb','훈제하다','To preserve or flavour food by exposing it to smoke.','He {smokes} the brisket for twelve hours over wood chips.','그는 나무 칩 위에서 12시간 동안 브리스켓을 훈제해요.','smokes','B2','cooking',1,'smoke brisket wood chips bbq'),
('w_cooking_B2_20','infuse','/ɪnˈfjuːz/','verb','우려내다','To allow flavours to pass into a liquid by soaking.','{Infuse} the oil with rosemary and garlic for added flavour.','풍미를 더하기 위해 기름에 로즈마리와 마늘을 우려 주세요.','Infuse','B2','cooking',1,'infuse oil rosemary herb flavor'),
('w_cooking_B2_21','texture','/ˈtɛkstʃər/','noun','식감','The feel of food in the mouth.','The creamy {texture} of the risotto was perfect.','리조또의 크리미한 식감이 완벽했어요.','texture','B2','cooking',1,'texture creamy risotto mouthfeel food'),
('w_cooking_B2_22','aroma','/əˈroʊmə/','noun','향기','A pleasant smell from food or drink.','The {aroma} of freshly baked bread filled the kitchen.','갓 구운 빵의 향기가 주방을 가득 채웠어요.','aroma','B2','cooking',1,'aroma bread baking kitchen smell'),
('w_cooking_B2_23','umami','/uːˈmɑːmi/','noun','우마미 (감칠맛)','A savoury fifth taste found in foods like mushrooms and soy sauce.','Adding miso paste boosts the {umami} of the broth.','미소 페이스트를 넣으면 육수의 감칠맛이 올라가요.','umami','B2','cooking',1,'umami savory miso broth fifth taste'),
('w_cooking_B2_24','savory','/ˈseɪvəri/','adjective','짭짤한 (풍미 있는)','Having a pleasant, non-sweet flavour.','She prefers {savory} dishes to sweet ones.','그녀는 달콤한 것보다 짭짤한 요리를 좋아해요.','savory','B2','cooking',1,'savory dish flavor herb non-sweet'),
('w_cooking_B2_25','bitter','/ˈbɪtər/','adjective','쓴','Having a sharp, unpleasant taste.','Dark chocolate has a pleasantly {bitter} flavour.','다크 초콜릿은 기분 좋게 쓴 풍미가 있어요.','bitter','B2','cooking',1,'bitter dark chocolate taste strong'),
('w_cooking_B2_26','acidity','/əˈsɪdɪti/','noun','산도','The level of acid in food or drink.','A squeeze of lemon adds brightness and {acidity} to the dish.','레몬 한 방울은 요리에 상쾌함과 산도를 더해 줘요.','acidity','B2','cooking',1,'acidity lemon vinegar bright cooking'),
('w_cooking_B2_27','balance','/ˈbæləns/','noun','균형','A harmonious combination of flavours in a dish.','The sauce has a perfect {balance} of sweet and sour.','그 소스는 달콤함과 신맛의 완벽한 균형을 이뤄요.','balance','B2','cooking',1,'balance flavor sweet sour cooking'),
('w_cooking_B2_28','contrast','/ˈkɒntræst/','noun','대비','A difference in taste, texture, or colour in a dish.','The crispy topping adds {contrast} to the creamy soup.','바삭한 토핑이 크리미한 수프에 대비를 더해 줘요.','contrast','B2','cooking',1,'contrast texture crispy creamy dish'),
('w_cooking_B2_29','pairing','/ˈpɛərɪŋ/','noun','페어링 (조합)','A combination of food and drink that complement each other.','The sommelier recommended a wine {pairing} for each course.','소믈리에가 코스별 와인 페어링을 추천해 줬어요.','pairing','B2','cooking',1,'pairing wine food combination course'),
('w_cooking_B2_30','fusion','/ˈfjuːʒən/','noun','퓨전','A style of cooking that blends two different culinary traditions.','The restaurant serves Japanese-Mexican {fusion} cuisine.','그 레스토랑은 일본-멕시코 퓨전 요리를 제공해요.','fusion','B2','cooking',1,'fusion cuisine mix japanese mexican creative'),
('w_cooking_B2_31','artisan','/ˈɑːrtɪzən/','adjective','장인의','Made by hand using traditional methods.','They sell {artisan} bread made fresh every morning.','그들은 매일 아침 신선하게 만든 장인 빵을 판매해요.','artisan','B2','cooking',1,'artisan bread handmade traditional craft'),
('w_cooking_B2_32','sustainable','/səˈsteɪnəbəl/','adjective','지속 가능한','Causing little or no environmental damage.','The restaurant is committed to {sustainable} sourcing.','그 레스토랑은 지속 가능한 식재료 조달에 힘쓰고 있어요.','sustainable','B2','cooking',1,'sustainable sourcing environment farm ethical'),
('w_cooking_B2_33','organic sourcing','/ɔːrˈɡænɪk ˈsɔːrsɪŋ/','noun phrase','유기농 조달','The practice of obtaining ingredients grown without synthetic chemicals.','Their menu highlights {organic sourcing} from local farms.','메뉴에는 지역 농장의 유기농 조달이 강조되어 있어요.','organic sourcing','B2','cooking',1,'organic farm local produce natural'),
('w_cooking_B2_34','farm-to-table','/ˌfɑːrm tə ˈteɪbəl/','adjective','농장에서 식탁으로','Describing food sourced directly from local farms.','The {farm-to-table} movement values freshness and locality.','농장에서 식탁으로 이어지는 운동은 신선함과 지역성을 중시해요.','farm-to-table','B2','cooking',1,'farm table local fresh produce market'),
('w_cooking_B2_35','zero waste','/ˈzɪəroʊ weɪst/','noun phrase','제로 웨이스트','A cooking approach that uses all parts of ingredients to minimize waste.','{Zero waste} cooking uses every part of the vegetable.','제로 웨이스트 요리는 채소의 모든 부분을 활용해요.','zero waste','B2','cooking',1,'zero waste cooking vegetable scraps sustainable'),
('w_cooking_C1_01','gastronomy','/ɡæˈstrɒnəmi/','noun','미식학','The art and science of good eating.','She studied {gastronomy} at a prestigious culinary institute.','그녀는 명망 있는 요리 연구소에서 미식학을 공부했어요.','gastronomy','C1','cooking',1,'gastronomy fine dining study culinary art'),
('w_cooking_C1_02','mise en place','/ˌmiːz ɒn ˈplɑːs/','noun','미장플라스','The preparation and arrangement of ingredients before cooking.','Professional chefs always practice {mise en place} before service.','전문 셰프는 항상 서비스 전에 미장플라스를 실천해요.','mise en place','C1','cooking',1,'mise en place prep organized kitchen professional'),
('w_cooking_C1_03','julienne','/ˌdʒuːliˈɛn/','verb','줄리엔 썰기하다','To cut food into thin matchstick-sized strips.','{Julienne} the carrots and add them to the salad.','당근을 줄리엔 썰기 하여 샐러드에 넣어 주세요.','Julienne','C1','cooking',1,'julienne carrot thin strip knife technique'),
('w_cooking_C1_04','brunoise','/ˈbruːnwɑːz/','noun','브루노아즈','Very finely diced cubes of vegetables, about 3mm.','Garnish the soup with a {brunoise} of carrot and celery.','수프를 당근과 셀러리 브루노아즈로 장식해 주세요.','brunoise','C1','cooking',1,'brunoise dice tiny cube vegetable technique'),
('w_cooking_C1_05','chiffonade','/ˌʃɪfəˈneɪd/','noun','시포나드','Leafy greens or herbs cut into very thin ribbons.','Top the dish with a {chiffonade} of fresh basil.','신선한 바질 시포나드로 요리 위에 올려 주세요.','chiffonade','C1','cooking',1,'chiffonade basil ribbon herb garnish'),
('w_cooking_C1_06','roux','/ruː/','noun','루 (소스 베이스)','A cooked mixture of equal parts fat and flour used to thicken sauces.','Make a {roux} by cooking butter and flour together for two minutes.','버터와 밀가루를 함께 2분 동안 볶아 루를 만들어 주세요.','roux','C1','cooking',1,'roux butter flour sauce base thicken'),
('w_cooking_C1_07','velouté','/vəˈluːteɪ/','noun','벨루테 소스','A classic French sauce made from light stock thickened with a roux.','The chef prepared a delicate fish {velouté} to start the meal.','셰프는 식사의 시작으로 섬세한 피시 벨루테를 준비했어요.','velouté','C1','cooking',1,'velouté sauce french classic light stock'),
('w_cooking_C1_08','béchamel','/ˌbeɪʃəˈmɛl/','noun','베샤멜 소스','A white sauce made from milk, butter, and flour.','Layer the lasagne with {béchamel} sauce between each sheet.','각 시트 사이에 베샤멜 소스를 겹겹이 쌓아 주세요.','béchamel','C1','cooking',1,'béchamel white sauce creamy lasagne french'),
('w_cooking_C1_09','espagnole','/ˌɛspəˈnjɒl/','noun','에스파뇰 소스','A rich brown sauce made from beef stock and tomatoes.','The {espagnole} sauce forms the base of many classic French dishes.','에스파뇰 소스는 많은 클래식 프랑스 요리의 기반이 돼요.','espagnole','C1','cooking',1,'espagnole brown sauce classic french beef'),
('w_cooking_C1_10','hollandaise','/ˌhɒlənˈdeɪz/','noun','올란데즈 소스','An emulsified sauce made from egg yolks and clarified butter.','Eggs Benedict is served with a rich {hollandaise} sauce.','에그 베네딕트에는 풍부한 올란데즈 소스가 제공돼요.','hollandaise','C1','cooking',1,'hollandaise sauce egg butter emulsified rich'),
('w_cooking_C1_11','sous vide','/ˌsuː ˈviːd/','noun','수비드','A cooking method where food is vacuum-sealed and cooked in water at a precise temperature.','The steak was cooked {sous vide} at 55°C for two hours.','스테이크는 55°C에서 2시간 동안 수비드로 조리됐어요.','sous vide','C1','cooking',1,'sous vide vacuum precision temperature water bath'),
('w_cooking_C1_12','confit','/kɒnˈfiː/','noun','콩피','A cooking technique where food is cooked and preserved in its own fat.','Duck {confit} is a classic dish from the Gascony region.','오리 콩피는 가스코뉴 지방의 클래식 요리예요.','confit','C1','cooking',1,'confit duck fat preserve french classic'),
('w_cooking_C1_13','terrine','/təˈriːn/','noun','테린','A dish of ground meat or vegetables packed tightly into a loaf shape.','The chef prepared a country-style pork {terrine} as a starter.','셰프는 전채로 시골식 돼지고기 테린을 준비했어요.','terrine','C1','cooking',1,'terrine pork loaf french starter slice'),
('w_cooking_C1_14','ceviche','/səˈviːtʃi/','noun','세비체','A dish of raw fish cured in citrus juice.','She made a refreshing {ceviche} with lime, cilantro, and chili.','그녀는 라임, 고수, 고추로 상쾌한 세비체를 만들었어요.','ceviche','C1','cooking',1,'ceviche fish lime citrus raw fresh'),
('w_cooking_C1_15','mirepoix','/ˌmɪərˈpwɑː/','noun','미르푸아','A mixture of diced onion, carrot, and celery used as a flavour base.','Start the soup by softening a {mirepoix} in butter.','버터에 미르푸아를 볶아 수프를 시작해 주세요.','mirepoix','C1','cooking',1,'mirepoix onion carrot celery base french'),
('w_cooking_C1_16','bouquet garni','/buːˌkeɪ ɡɑːrˈniː/','noun','부케 가르니','A bundle of herbs tied together and used to flavour stocks and stews.','Add a {bouquet garni} to the stew and remove it before serving.','스튜에 부케 가르니를 넣고 제공 전에 꺼내 주세요.','bouquet garni','C1','cooking',1,'bouquet garni herbs bundle stock stew'),
('w_cooking_C1_17','dehydrate','/ˌdiːhaɪˈdreɪt/','verb','탈수시키다','To remove moisture from food to preserve it.','She {dehydrates} fruit slices to make healthy snacks.','그녀는 건강한 간식을 만들기 위해 과일 조각을 탈수시켜요.','dehydrates','C1','cooking',1,'dehydrate fruit slice machine preservation'),
('w_cooking_C1_18','spherification','/ˌsfɪərɪfɪˈkeɪʃən/','noun','구체화 기법','A molecular technique that creates liquid-filled gel spheres.','He used {spherification} to make olive oil pearls for the dish.','그는 요리를 위해 구체화 기법으로 올리브오일 펄을 만들었어요.','spherification','C1','cooking',1,'spherification molecular cooking sphere modern'),
('w_cooking_C1_19','emulsion','/ɪˈmʌlʃən/','noun','에멀전','A stable mixture of two liquids that normally do not mix.','A good vinaigrette is a stable oil and vinegar {emulsion}.','좋은 비네그레트는 오일과 식초의 안정적인 에멀전이에요.','emulsion','C1','cooking',1,'emulsion oil vinegar stable sauce cooking'),
('w_cooking_C1_20','foam','/foʊm/','noun','폼 (거품)','An airy culinary preparation made by incorporating air into liquid.','The dessert was topped with a light vanilla {foam}.','디저트 위에 가벼운 바닐라 폼이 올려졌어요.','foam','C1','cooking',1,'foam vanilla dessert airy modern culinary'),
('w_cooking_C1_21','gel','/dʒɛl/','noun','겔 (응고물)','A jelly-like food preparation made with a gelling agent.','The mango {gel} was made using agar-agar.','망고 겔은 한천을 사용하여 만들었어요.','gel','C1','cooking',1,'gel agar mango modern cuisine setting'),
('w_cooking_C1_22','molecular gastronomy','/məˌlɛkjʊlər ɡæˈstrɒnəmi/','noun','분자 미식학','A scientific approach to cooking that explores physical and chemical changes.','The restaurant is famous for its {molecular gastronomy} tasting menu.','그 레스토랑은 분자 미식학 시식 메뉴로 유명해요.','molecular gastronomy','C1','cooking',1,'molecular gastronomy modern science cooking lab'),
('w_cooking_C1_23','umami enhancement','/uːˈmɑːmi ɪnˈhɑːnsmənt/','noun phrase','감칠맛 강화','Techniques or ingredients that intensify the savoury fifth taste.','Adding anchovies is a classic method of {umami enhancement}.','멸치를 넣는 것은 감칠맛 강화의 클래식 방법이에요.','umami enhancement','C1','cooking',1,'umami anchovy flavor enhancement savory cooking'),
('w_cooking_C1_24','Maillard reaction','/maɪˈɑːr riˈækʃən/','noun','마이야르 반응','The chemical reaction between amino acids and sugars that gives browned food its flavour.','The {Maillard reaction} is responsible for the crust on a seared steak.','마이야르 반응은 구운 스테이크의 겉껍질 형성에 기여해요.','Maillard reaction','C1','cooking',1,'maillard reaction sear steak crust browning'),
('w_cooking_C1_25','caramelization','/ˌkærəməlaɪˈzeɪʃən/','noun','캐러멜화 반응','The browning of sugar due to heat, producing a sweet, nutty flavour.','Slow cooking brings out {caramelization} in the onions.','천천히 익히면 양파에서 캐러멜화 반응이 일어나요.','caramelization','C1','cooking',1,'caramelization sugar brown heat onion sweet'),
('w_cooking_C1_26','thermodynamics of cooking','/ˌθɜːrmoʊdaɪˈnæmɪks/','noun phrase','요리의 열역학','The study of how heat transfers in the cooking process.','Understanding the {thermodynamics of cooking} helps chefs control texture.','요리의 열역학을 이해하면 셰프가 식감을 조절하는 데 도움이 돼요.','thermodynamics of cooking','C1','cooking',1,'thermodynamics heat cooking science transfer'),
('w_cooking_C1_27','maceration','/ˌmæsəˈreɪʃən/','noun','마세라시옹 (침지)','Soaking food in liquid to soften it or extract flavour.','{Maceration} in red wine softens the dried fruit beautifully.','레드와인에 마세라시옹하면 말린 과일이 아름답게 부드러워져요.','Maceration','C1','cooking',1,'maceration wine fruit soak flavor extract'),
('w_cooking_C1_28','osmosis','/ɒzˈmoʊsɪs/','noun','삼투압','The movement of water through a membrane, important in salting and marinating.','{Osmosis} draws moisture out of vegetables when salt is applied.','소금을 뿌리면 삼투압 작용으로 채소에서 수분이 빠져나와요.','Osmosis','C1','cooking',1,'osmosis salt vegetable science moisture'),
('w_cooking_C1_29','flavor compound','/ˈfleɪvər ˈkɒmpaʊnd/','noun phrase','향미 화합물','A chemical substance that contributes to the taste or smell of food.','Each {flavor compound} in vanilla creates a distinct sensory experience.','바닐라의 각 향미 화합물은 독특한 감각 경험을 만들어 줘요.','flavor compound','C1','cooking',1,'flavor compound chemical vanilla aroma science'),
('w_cooking_C1_30','volatile aroma','/ˈvɒlətaɪl əˈroʊmə/','noun phrase','휘발성 향기','Aromatic molecules that evaporate and are detected by smell.','The {volatile aroma} of fresh coffee diminishes quickly once brewed.','갓 끓인 커피의 휘발성 향기는 빠르게 줄어들어요.','volatile aroma','C1','cooking',1,'volatile aroma coffee evaporate smell sensory'),
('w_cooking_C1_31','palate','/ˈpælɪt/','noun','미각','A person''s ability to taste and judge food.','She has a refined {palate} for distinguishing wine regions.','그녀는 와인 지역을 구분할 수 있는 세련된 미각을 가지고 있어요.','palate','C1','cooking',1,'palate taste refined wine sensory'),
('w_cooking_C1_32','sensory evaluation','/ˈsɛnsəri ɪˌvæljuˈeɪʃən/','noun phrase','관능 평가','The scientific assessment of food using the five senses.','The lab conducted a {sensory evaluation} of the new sauce recipe.','연구소는 새로운 소스 레시피에 대한 관능 평가를 실시했어요.','sensory evaluation','C1','cooking',1,'sensory evaluation lab taste smell food science'),
('w_cooking_C1_33','food science','/fuːd saɪəns/','noun','식품 과학','The study of the physical, chemical, and biological properties of food.','Advances in {food science} have improved food preservation techniques.','식품 과학의 발전은 식품 보존 기술을 향상시켰어요.','food science','C1','cooking',1,'food science lab chemistry biology study'),
('w_cooking_C1_34','nutritional profile','/njuːˈtrɪʃənl ˈproʊfaɪl/','noun phrase','영양 성분 프로파일','A summary of the nutrients found in a food.','The {nutritional profile} of quinoa is superior to most grains.','퀴노아의 영양 성분 프로파일은 대부분의 곡물보다 우수해요.','nutritional profile','C1','cooking',1,'nutritional profile grain label healthy analysis'),
('w_cooking_C1_35','culinary tradition','/ˈkʌlɪnəri trəˈdɪʃən/','noun phrase','요리 전통','The inherited cooking practices of a particular culture.','The chef draws inspiration from Korean {culinary tradition}.','그 셰프는 한국 요리 전통에서 영감을 받아요.','culinary tradition','C1','cooking',1,'culinary tradition culture heritage recipe passed'),
('w_cooking_C2_01','organoleptic','/ˌɔːrɡənəˈlɛptɪk/','adjective','관능적인 (오감과 관련된)','Relating to the senses of taste, smell, and sight as applied to food.','The {organoleptic} properties of the dish were rigorously tested.','그 요리의 관능적 특성이 엄격하게 테스트됐어요.','organoleptic','C2','cooking',1,'organoleptic senses taste smell food testing'),
('w_cooking_C2_02','oleic acid','/oʊˈliːɪk ˈæsɪd/','noun','올레산','A monounsaturated fatty acid found mainly in olive oil.','Extra virgin olive oil is rich in {oleic acid}.','엑스트라 버진 올리브 오일은 올레산이 풍부해요.','oleic acid','C2','cooking',1,'oleic acid olive oil fatty acid nutrition'),
('w_cooking_C2_03','anthocyanin','/ˌænθəˈsaɪənɪn/','noun','안토시아닌','A blue or purple pigment in plants with antioxidant properties.','The deep purple colour of blueberries comes from {anthocyanin}.','블루베리의 짙은 보라색은 안토시아닌에서 비롯돼요.','anthocyanin','C2','cooking',1,'anthocyanin blueberry purple pigment antioxidant'),
('w_cooking_C2_04','polyphenol','/ˌpɒliˈfiːnɒl/','noun','폴리페놀','A plant-based antioxidant compound found in fruits, vegetables, and wine.','Red wine contains {polyphenols} that may benefit cardiovascular health.','레드와인에는 심혈관 건강에 도움이 될 수 있는 폴리페놀이 함유돼 있어요.','polyphenols','C2','cooking',1,'polyphenol red wine antioxidant plant health'),
('w_cooking_C2_05','antioxidant','/ˌæntiˈɒksɪdənt/','noun','항산화제','A substance that protects cells from damage caused by free radicals.','Blueberries are one of the best natural sources of {antioxidants}.','블루베리는 최고의 천연 항산화제 공급원 중 하나예요.','antioxidants','C2','cooking',1,'antioxidant blueberry health protect natural'),
('w_cooking_C2_06','bioavailability','/ˌbaɪoʊəˌveɪləˈbɪlɪti/','noun','생체이용률','The proportion of a nutrient that is absorbed and used by the body.','Cooking tomatoes increases the {bioavailability} of lycopene.','토마토를 익히면 리코펜의 생체이용률이 높아져요.','bioavailability','C2','cooking',1,'bioavailability nutrient absorbed body tomato'),
('w_cooking_C2_07','glycemic index','/ɡlaɪˌsiːmɪk ˈɪndɛks/','noun','혈당 지수','A measure of how quickly a food raises blood sugar levels.','Brown rice has a lower {glycemic index} than white rice.','현미는 흰쌀보다 혈당 지수가 낮아요.','glycemic index','C2','cooking',1,'glycemic index blood sugar rice nutrition'),
('w_cooking_C2_08','lipid oxidation','/ˈlɪpɪd ˌɒksɪˈdeɪʃən/','noun','지방 산화','The chemical process by which fats react with oxygen and become rancid.','Proper storage prevents {lipid oxidation} in cooking oils.','적절한 보관은 식용유의 지방 산화를 방지해요.','lipid oxidation','C2','cooking',1,'lipid oxidation fat rancid oil storage'),
('w_cooking_C2_09','protein denaturation','/ˈproʊtiːn ˌdiːnætʃəˈreɪʃən/','noun','단백질 변성','The process by which proteins lose their structure when exposed to heat or acid.','{Protein denaturation} is why egg whites become firm when cooked.','단백질 변성 때문에 달걀 흰자가 익으면 단단해지는 거예요.','Protein denaturation','C2','cooking',1,'protein denaturation egg heat science cooking'),
('w_cooking_C2_10','starch gelatinization','/stɑːrtʃ dʒɪˌlætɪnaɪˈzeɪʃən/','noun','전분 호화','The process by which starch granules absorb water and swell when heated.','{Starch gelatinization} is what makes sauces thick when cooked.','전분 호화 때문에 소스가 익으면 걸쭉해지는 거예요.','Starch gelatinization','C2','cooking',1,'starch gelatinization sauce thick heat science'),
('w_cooking_C2_11','fermentation chemistry','/ˌfɜːrmənˈteɪʃən ˈkɛmɪstri/','noun','발효 화학','The biochemical processes carried out by microorganisms during fermentation.','Understanding {fermentation chemistry} is key to brewing and baking.','발효 화학을 이해하는 것은 양조와 베이킹의 핵심이에요.','fermentation chemistry','C2','cooking',1,'fermentation chemistry microbe biology brewing'),
('w_cooking_C2_12','enzymatic browning','/ˌɛnzaɪˈmætɪk ˈbraʊnɪŋ/','noun','효소적 갈변','The browning of cut fruit or vegetables caused by enzymes reacting with oxygen.','{Enzymatic browning} turns sliced apples brown quickly.','효소적 갈변 때문에 잘린 사과가 빠르게 갈색으로 변해요.','Enzymatic browning','C2','cooking',1,'enzymatic browning apple cut oxygen enzyme'),
('w_cooking_C2_13','non-enzymatic browning','/ˌnɒn ˌɛnzaɪˈmætɪk ˈbraʊnɪŋ/','noun','비효소적 갈변','Browning caused by heat reactions such as the Maillard reaction or caramelization.','{Non-enzymatic browning} gives baked goods their golden colour and rich aroma.','비효소적 갈변이 구운 음식에 황금색과 풍부한 향을 줘요.','Non-enzymatic browning','C2','cooking',1,'non-enzymatic browning maillard baking golden crust'),
('w_cooking_C2_14','collagen hydrolysis','/ˈkɒlədʒən haɪˈdrɒlɪsɪs/','noun','콜라겐 가수분해','The breakdown of collagen into gelatin during slow cooking.','{Collagen hydrolysis} is responsible for the silky texture of slow-cooked broths.','콜라겐 가수분해 덕분에 천천히 끓인 육수가 실크처럼 부드러워요.','Collagen hydrolysis','C2','cooking',1,'collagen hydrolysis gelatin broth slow cooking'),
('w_cooking_C2_15','emulsification physics','/ɪˌmʌlsɪfɪˈkeɪʃən ˈfɪzɪks/','noun','유화의 물리학','The physical principles governing the formation and stability of emulsions.','{Emulsification physics} explains why vinaigrette separates over time.','유화의 물리학은 비네그레트가 시간이 지나면 분리되는 이유를 설명해요.','Emulsification physics','C2','cooking',1,'emulsification physics oil water stability science'),
('w_cooking_C2_16','surfactant','/ˈsɜːrfæktənt/','noun','계면활성제','A substance that stabilizes emulsions by reducing surface tension.','Lecithin acts as a natural {surfactant} in egg-based sauces.','레시틴은 달걀 기반 소스에서 천연 계면활성제 역할을 해요.','surfactant','C2','cooking',1,'surfactant lecithin emulsion sauce science'),
('w_cooking_C2_17','hydrocolloid','/ˌhaɪdrəˈkɒlɔɪd/','noun','하이드로콜로이드','A substance that forms a gel when combined with water, used as a food thickener.','Xanthan gum is a {hydrocolloid} used in gluten-free baking.','잔탄검은 글루텐 프리 베이킹에 사용되는 하이드로콜로이드예요.','hydrocolloid','C2','cooking',1,'hydrocolloid xanthan gum thickener baking gel'),
('w_cooking_C2_18','rheology','/riːˈɒlədʒi/','noun','유변학','The study of how materials flow and deform, relevant to texture in cooking.','The {rheology} of chocolate is critical for tempering and moulding.','초콜릿의 유변학은 템퍼링과 몰딩에 매우 중요해요.','rheology','C2','cooking',1,'rheology chocolate texture flow science'),
('w_cooking_C2_19','viscosity','/vɪˈskɒsɪti/','noun','점도','The thickness and resistance to flow of a liquid food.','The {viscosity} of the sauce determines how it coats the pasta.','소스의 점도가 파스타에 어떻게 코팅되는지를 결정해요.','viscosity','C2','cooking',1,'viscosity sauce thick flow coating pasta'),
('w_cooking_C2_20','sensory threshold','/ˈsɛnsəri ˈθrɛʃhoʊld/','noun','감각 역치','The minimum concentration of a substance needed for it to be detected by the senses.','The {sensory threshold} for bitterness varies between individuals.','쓴맛의 감각 역치는 사람마다 달라요.','sensory threshold','C2','cooking',1,'sensory threshold bitter taste individual science'),
('w_cooking_C2_21','olfactory receptor','/ɒlˈfæktəri rɪˈsɛptər/','noun','후각 수용체','A nerve cell in the nose that detects aroma molecules.','Each {olfactory receptor} responds to specific aroma compounds.','각 후각 수용체는 특정 향기 화합물에 반응해요.','olfactory receptor','C2','cooking',1,'olfactory receptor nose aroma smell science'),
('w_cooking_C2_22','gustatory','/ˈɡʌstətɔːri/','adjective','미각의','Relating to the sense of taste.','The {gustatory} experience of the dish was complex and layered.','그 요리의 미각적 경험은 복잡하고 다층적이었어요.','gustatory','C2','cooking',1,'gustatory taste sense food experience complex'),
('w_cooking_C2_23','retronasal olfaction','/ˌrɛtrəˈneɪzəl ɒlˈfækʃən/','noun','후비강 후각','The perception of aroma through the back of the mouth while eating.','{Retronasal olfaction} is a key component of how we experience flavour.','후비강 후각은 우리가 풍미를 경험하는 방식의 핵심 요소예요.','Retronasal olfaction','C2','cooking',1,'retronasal olfaction aroma mouth flavor science'),
('w_cooking_C2_24','flavor perception','/ˈfleɪvər pərˈsɛpʃən/','noun','풍미 인식','The overall sensory experience of tasting food.','{Flavor perception} is influenced by both taste and smell simultaneously.','풍미 인식은 미각과 후각에 동시에 영향을 받아요.','Flavor perception','C2','cooking',1,'flavor perception sensory taste smell brain'),
('w_cooking_C2_25','terroir','/tɛˈrwɑːr/','noun','테루아르','The environmental conditions of a place that give its produce a unique character.','The olive oil reflects the {terroir} of the Cretan hillsides.','그 올리브 오일은 크레타 언덕의 테루아르를 반영해요.','terroir','C2','cooking',1,'terroir environment olive oil place character'),
('w_cooking_C2_26','provenance','/ˈprɒvənəns/','noun','원산지','The origin or source of an ingredient.','The menu lists the {provenance} of every ingredient used.','메뉴에는 사용된 모든 재료의 원산지가 나와 있어요.','provenance','C2','cooking',1,'provenance origin ingredient menu traceability'),
('w_cooking_C2_27','indigenous ingredient','/ɪnˈdɪdʒɪnəs ɪnˈɡriːdiənt/','noun phrase','토착 재료','An ingredient native to and traditionally used in a specific region.','The chef celebrates {indigenous ingredients} from the Amazon rainforest.','셰프는 아마존 열대우림의 토착 재료를 기념해요.','indigenous ingredients','C2','cooking',1,'indigenous ingredient native region amazon local'),
('w_cooking_C2_28','food sovereignty','/fuːd ˈsɒvrənti/','noun','식량 주권','The right of people to define their own food systems and policies.','{Food sovereignty} empowers communities to protect traditional crops.','식량 주권은 지역 사회가 전통 작물을 보호할 수 있도록 해요.','Food sovereignty','C2','cooking',1,'food sovereignty rights community traditional crops'),
('w_cooking_C2_29','culinary anthropology','/ˈkʌlɪnəri ˌænθrəˈpɒlədʒi/','noun','요리 인류학','The study of how food practices reflect human culture and society.','{Culinary anthropology} reveals how migration shapes national cuisines.','요리 인류학은 이주가 국가 요리를 어떻게 형성하는지 보여 줘요.','Culinary anthropology','C2','cooking',1,'culinary anthropology culture society food migration'),
('w_cooking_C2_30','gastronomic heritage','/ˌɡæstrəˈnɒmɪk ˈhɛrɪtɪdʒ/','noun phrase','미식 유산','The traditional food practices and knowledge passed down through generations.','UNESCO recognized French cuisine as part of global {gastronomic heritage}.','유네스코는 프랑스 요리를 세계 미식 유산의 일부로 인정했어요.','gastronomic heritage','C2','cooking',1,'gastronomic heritage UNESCO france tradition culture'),
('w_cooking_C2_31','nutritional epidemiology','/njuːˌtrɪʃənl ˌɛpɪˌdiːmiˈɒlədʒi/','noun','영양 역학','The study of how diet affects health outcomes across populations.','{Nutritional epidemiology} has linked Mediterranean diets to longevity.','영양 역학은 지중해 식단과 장수를 연결 짓고 있어요.','Nutritional epidemiology','C2','cooking',1,'nutritional epidemiology diet health mediterranean study'),
('w_cooking_C2_32','dietary pattern','/ˈdaɪətəri ˈpætərn/','noun','식이 패턴','The overall combination of foods regularly consumed by a person or population.','A plant-based {dietary pattern} is associated with better long-term health.','식물성 식이 패턴은 장기적인 건강과 관련이 있어요.','dietary pattern','C2','cooking',1,'dietary pattern plant-based health study population'),
('w_cooking_C2_33','food systems','/fuːd ˈsɪstəmz/','noun','식품 시스템','The complete network of activities involved in producing, distributing, and consuming food.','Sustainable {food systems} must address both nutrition and environmental impact.','지속 가능한 식품 시스템은 영양과 환경 영향을 모두 다루어야 해요.','food systems','C2','cooking',1,'food systems network production distribution sustainability'),
('w_cooking_C2_34','agrobiodiversity','/ˌæɡrəʊˌbaɪoʊdaɪˈvɜːrsɪti/','noun','농업 생물 다양성','The variety of plants and animals used in agriculture and food production.','Protecting {agrobiodiversity} safeguards future food security.','농업 생물 다양성을 보호하면 미래 식량 안보를 지킬 수 있어요.','agrobiodiversity','C2','cooking',1,'agrobiodiversity crops diversity agriculture ecosystem'),
('w_cooking_C2_35','culinary semiotics','/ˈkʌlɪnəri ˌsiːmiˈɒtɪks/','noun','요리 기호학','The study of food as a system of signs and symbols in culture.','{Culinary semiotics} explores why certain foods carry cultural meaning.','요리 기호학은 왜 특정 음식이 문화적 의미를 담는지 탐구해요.','Culinary semiotics','C2','cooking',1,'culinary semiotics food symbol culture meaning')
